We bridge the gap between emerging technologies and fintech regulations that are slow to adapt. In the process, we help companies leverage new technology and find market opportunities in an increasingly competitive environment. Our lawyers work across offices in the United States, Europe and Asia, drawing on decades of experience to advise key players in the biggest global fintech markets. Clients relying on our solutions range from large financial institutions with operations spanning many countries to entrepreneurial companies launching their businesses in a single jurisdiction. Learn more.

name: Decrypting Money
description:
Bitcoin is more than an investment. It’s more than electronic cash, or a form of payment. Bitcoin is security, equality, and independence. Bitcoin is gold—a gold tailor-made for the internet age.

In our book, Decrypting Money, cryptocurrency experts Marco Krohn, Anthony Jefferies, Marco Streng, and Zoran Balkic pull back the curtain on the world of public ledgers, decentralization, mining, blockchains, and private keys. They reveal a place where printing presses cannot debase money and funds are safely—and quickly—transferred over insecure networks. Without technical jargon or complicated formulae, this insightful resource provides everyone from the bitcoin novice to the experienced user with background knowledge on the history of money, the characteristics of sound money, and the deep rabbit hole of cryptocurrencies. Decrypting Money is the jumpstart you need to understand cryptocurrencies and make your money truly yours.

In 2023, DTCC’s subsidiaries processed securities transactions valued at U.S. $3 quadrillion and its depository subsidiary provided custody and asset servicing for securities issues from over 150 countries and territories valued at U.S. $85 trillion. description:
Floki is the people’s cryptocurrency and the utility token of the Floki Ecosystem. Floki originally started as a meme token inspired by Elon Musk, but has since evolved into a robust ecosystem with several utility products and one of the most recognized crypto brands in the world.

The Floki Ecosystem consists of utility products aimed at helping people take control of their finances using decentralized technology. These utility products include:

- The Valhalla PlayToEarn NFT metaverse game, which features novel on-chain gaming mechanics.
- The FlokiFi Locker protocol which is the most innovative crypto locker protocol in the industry.
- The Floki Staking program, which allows users to stake their $FLOKI tokens and earn Floki's sister token, TokenFi ($TOKEN). 
- TokenFi, which is an all-in-one tokenization platform for creating tokens and tokenizing assets in a few clicks using a simple interface without touching a line of code.
- The University of Floki crypto education platform.

In addition to Floki's strong utility focus, we also deeply value philanthropy. Floki has built schools in four different nations of the world; Nigeria, Ghana, Laos, and Guatemala respectively.

Floki has also made a series of strong marketing efforts that has made us one of the most recognized crypto brands in the world. These include partnerships with 8 major international football clubs, a top Formula 1 team, major cricket teams in India, Badminton Asia, ITTF World Table Tennis, and more. Combined, these partnerships have introduced the Floki brand to well over 3.5 billion people globally.

Whether you’re valuing token grants, intricate warrants, or you are dealing with the issuance of tokens as part of a more sophisticated transaction, Teknos Associates is able to innovate and aid our clients in finding the solution that bests fits your needs.

name: Teleport
description:
Teleport is the first client for The Rideshare Protocol (TRIP). 

TRIP is an open protocol, built on Solana, that frees the rideshare market so that drivers earn more and riders pay less.

name: Tezos
description: Tezos is a scalable, energy-efficient blockchain ecosystem and open-source platform for assets and applications, with a strong focus on security, upgradeability, and on-chain community governance. It empowers builders, developers, and businesses to deploy applications securely and at low cost. Through the efforts of its global community of developers, the protocol is evolving into a modular, interoperable multi-layer blockchain ecosystem - where L1 handles security, and L2 rollups offer performance, flexibility, and compatibility with mainstream programming languages, with a data availability layer to boost scalability and security.

name: The Quantum Resistant Ledger
description: A purpose built, industrial-grade, future-forward and provably secure decentralized network and cryptocurrency resistant to the imminent advent of Quantum Computing.

name: Toledo Museum of Art
description: The Toledo Museum of Art (TMA) is a transformative institution that invites everyone to see differently, enriching lives through the power of art and pioneering the future of museum experiences through technological innovation. Its extensive and diverse collection, innovative educational programs, and community outreach foster a deep appreciation for art among its visitors. As a leader in integrating cutting-edge technology through initiatives like TMA Labs, TMA creates immersive, interactive experiences that redefine traditional museum engagement

name: Vyvo Smart Chain
description: Vyvo Smart Chain is a blockchain infrastructure that allows people to monetize, and be rewarded for their health data. People that utilize wearable devices to track and learn how to improve their health are able to use our blockchain to link their device to a Data-NFT, where the health data is then anonymized and able to be sold. Our infrastructure bridges wearable device users with institutional data buyers through blockchain technology. By leveraging this technology, we enable people to truly own their data and have rights in data monetization, while simultaneously providing data buyers with the ability to transparently purchase authenticated and unaltered data.

name: Wachsman
description: Founded in 2015, Wachsman is a leading global strategy and communications firm advising the next generation in Web3, disruptive technologies, fintech and venture capital. With offices across the globe in New York, Los Angeles, Washington, D.C, London, Dublin, Geneva, and Singapore, Wachsman has established its position as a trusted advisor to some of the most innovative companies around the world.

name: Walkers
description: Walkers is a leading international law firm. We provide legal, corporate, compliance and fiduciary services to global corporations, financial institutions, capital markets participants and investment fund managers. Our clients are the most innovative firms and institutions across the financial markets, and rely on us for our ability to provide solutions to their most important legal and business issues. We develop globally-minded, entrepreneurial lawyers who are experts in their field and committed to client service. Walkers is consistently ranked in the top tier of the leading global legal directories. Recognized for being a 'dynamic team that is very user friendly', a regular comment by clients is that Walkers is the "go-to" firm for offshore legal advice.

name: Web3Auth
description: Web3Auth is the leading key infrastructure provider, enabling seamless Web3 logins for everyone. Our solution provides 2-factor passwordless authentication with MPC and non-custodial key infrastructure for apps and wallets.

name: White & Case LLP
description:
White & Case is a global law firm with longstanding offices in the markets that matter today. Our on-the-ground experience, our cross-border integration and our depth of local, US and English-qualified lawyers help our clients work with confidence in any one market or across many.

We guide our clients through difficult issues, bringing our insight and judgment to each situation. Our innovative approaches create original solutions to our clients' most complex domestic and multijurisdictional deals and disputes.

By thinking on behalf of our clients every day, we anticipate what they want, provide what they need and build lasting relationships. We do what it takes to help our clients achieve their ambitions.

name: Willkie Farr & Gallagher
description: Willkie is an elite international law firm of approximately 1,200 lawyers based in thirteen offices in six countries. We represent companies across a wide spectrum of business areas and industries. Our core practices include M&A, private equity, asset management, bankruptcy and restructuring, complex litigation, and competition and antitrust. The firm comprises attorneys who are individually and as a group recognized as some of the world’s foremost subject-matter advisors in their respective areas of practice. We are committed to continuing our 130-year history of excellence and service to our clients.

name: Withersworldwide
description: The Withers crypto and digital assets team provides bespoke regulatory, litigation and arbitration services to clients in the DeFi, crypto and fintech industries. Our team has a proven track record of successfully representing clients in complex disputes and are known for our strategic and innovative approach.  We have a deep understanding of the rapidly evolving regulatory framework facing individuals and entities operating in these fast-paced spaces.

name: Withum
description: Withum is a forward-thinking, technology-driven advisory and accounting firm that has a deep level of expertise relating to all of the issues that arise within today’s ever-changing digital asset and blockchain technology environments. Our experienced professionals can help you navigate the intricate tax and accounting nuances of the digital asset and blockchain technology industry while ensuring you feel valued every step of the way and reach your ultimate goal.

name: WOW EARN
description: WOW EARN is an ecosystem with array of cutting edge Web3 solutions including WOW EARN Wallet, WOW EARN Chain, Mining, Staking, Swap & so much more!

name: Yala
description: Yala connects Bitcoin liquidity with a meta yield stablecoin. Designed as both a potent asset and a liquidity enhancer, the stablecoin, YU, operates across various ecosystems, increasing efficiency without the need for bridges or relocating the underlying Bitcoin. Yala empowers Bitcoin holders and ecosystem participants with expanded utility, all while maintaining the security of Bitcoin's infrastructure.

name: BLKWeb3
description: BLKWeb3 (BLKW3B) is a global ecosystem of Black Web3 builders, founders, creatives, allies and partners, focused on equity. The BLKW3B ecosystem works to address equity in Web3 through a number of powerful industry initiatives. By focusing on equity, BLKW3B calls for an entirely new approach to engaging the global majority, as valued contributors and active builders, who are shaping the greater web3 industry and thereby, the world.

name: CoinTelegraph
description: Founded in 2013, Cointelegraph is the leading independent digital media resource covering a wide range of news on blockchain technology, crypto assets, and emerging fintech trends. Each day our team delivers the most accurate and up-to-date news from both the decentralized and centralized worlds. Our editorial content is based on our passion to deliver unbiased news, in-depth analytics, comprehensive cryptocurrency price charts, insightful opinion pieces, as well as regular reports on the social transformation that digital currencies bring. We believe that the decentralized world will grow exponentially, becoming an integral part of our daily lives. We work every day to help educate our readers and raise awareness of the intricacies and advantages offered in today’s digital revolution. With technology breakthroughs now occurring in fields such as AI, VR, nanotech, quantum computing, and an increasing number of businesses, entrepreneurs and consumers adopting blockchain technology in everyday life, we aim to inform, educate, and share valuable information with our readers.

name: Defiant
description: The Defiant’s platform reaches 400,000 active DeFi investors, including the leading projects and funds, who trust our brand because we are the only information platform producing independent, DeFi-focused journalism—an “industry must-read” according to The New York Times, publishing high-quality, unbiased content daily.

name: Delphi Digital
description: Delphi Digital's Pro Research distills the complexities of the digital asset industry, offering deep, actionable insights for investors and industry leaders. Our proven track record since 2018 highlights our ability to consistently spotlight emerging opportunities and trends in the crypto space.

name: GlobalBoost Media
description: GlobalBoost Media is a decentralized free speech platform leveraging blockchain technology. Our Impact Money Show airs on TV in the 4th largest economy in the world.

name: TabbFORUM
description: TabbFORUM is the site for thought leadership on important issues affecting global capital markets.

name: Web3 Familia
description:
Web3 Familia is a global community & support network for founders & developers in web3.
Born in Nov 2021, to date we've hosted over 120 events, 6 hacker houses with over 5K attendees in 13 US cities and 8 international cities. We've partnered up with over 100 corporates, protocols, startups & VCs and given away over $200K in scholarships to our community. We are excited to once again be the official partner of Coindesk at Consensus and host the official Latinos in Web3 Meetup with programing focused on founders and developers in web3.

name: Web3event
description:
Web3event is the world's largest Web3 event aggregation platform, with over 40,000 global users.
Web3event.org aims to be the gateway to Web3 Events.
Our product focuses on Events Discovery, Create, Exposure, and People Connect.
